I have been waiting years
for a second chance.

33
00:00:10.243 --> 00:00:12.378
This is it.

34
00:00:16.616 --> 00:00:18.385
Ah!

35
00:00:18.618 --> 00:00:19.786
It's gonna be good!

36
00:00:19.953 --> 00:00:21.054
Ah!

37
00:04:14.187 --> 00:04:17.356
Aeron Bracken. worst
horseman among us.

38
00:04:19.692 --> 00:04:21.560
Must be my swordsmanship.

39
00:04:21.561 --> 00:04:24.230
Can you even get that thing up?

40
00:04:24.731 --> 00:04:26.531
Well enough for
killing Blackwoods.

41
00:04:26.532 --> 00:04:28.801
Bracken!

42
00:04:33.940 --> 00:04:37.143
Put the boundary stones back.

43
00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:39.511
We didn't move them.

44
00:04:39.512 --> 00:04:41.546
Oh. did they move
themselves. then?

45
00:04:41.547 --> 00:04:42.614
Just rolled their way over

46
00:04:42.615 --> 00:04:44.283
so Bracken cows can
fill their bellies

47
00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:46.285
- on Blackwood grass?
- The assize at Riverrun...

48
00:04:46.286 --> 00:04:47.954
Fuck the assize...

49
00:04:48.888 --> 00:04:50.323
and fuck you.

50
00:04:50.957 --> 00:04:52.358
This is our land.

51
00:04:58.665 --> 00:05:00.633
It's Bracken land.

52
00:05:04.203 --> 00:05:07.140
- Babe-killer.
- Davos Blackwood: What did you say?

53
00:05:11.778 --> 00:05:15.615
Your false queen.
Rhaenyra. is a kinslayer.

54
00:05:16.416 --> 00:05:20.053
Your uncle declared
for Aegon. did he?

55
00:05:22.755 --> 00:05:26.658
Well then. let me tell you

56
00:05:26.659 --> 00:05:32.064
Aegon Targaryen
is no true king...

57
00:05:32.065 --> 00:05:36.269
just as you are no true knight.

58
00:05:36.736 --> 00:05:40.940
You're both craven.
little cunts!

59
00:05:50.650 --> 00:05:53.185
You wouldn't dare.

60
00:06:34.694 --> 00:06:37.296
He is the basest of villains.

61
00:06:37.730 --> 00:06:40.133
He sullies the grave
of his brother.

62
00:06:41.801 --> 00:06:44.903
I cannot fault him
for keeping his oath.

63
00:06:47.707 --> 00:06:50.309
And what of those who sent him?

64
00:07:11.397 --> 00:07:14.634
Otto Hightower would
never have allowed this.

65
00:07:16.569 --> 00:07:19.372
Hotter blood has
prevailed. I think.

66
00:07:20.206 --> 00:07:22.140
The young men have taken
the bit in their teeth.

67
00:07:22.141 --> 00:07:24.377
They wish to punish. to avenge.

68
00:07:26.345 --> 00:07:28.313
Soon they will not even
remember what it was

69
00:07:28.314 --> 00:07:30.549
that began the war
in the first place.

70
00:07:30.550 --> 00:07:33.252
That is easy enough.
They usurped my throne.

71
00:07:33.486 --> 00:07:35.120
That is one answer.

72
00:07:39.125 --> 00:07:41.961
Or was it when the
child was beheaded?

73
00:07:43.996 --> 00:07:46.799
Or when Aemond killed Luke...

74
00:07:49.836 --> 00:07:52.939
or when Luke took Aemond's eye?

75
00:07:53.706 --> 00:07:56.809
We teeter now at the point
where none of it will matter.

76
00:07:58.044 --> 00:08:00.479
And the desire to kill
and burn takes hold

77
00:08:00.480 --> 00:08:02.715
and reason is forgotten.

78
00:08:04.584 --> 00:08:06.785
There may be another way.

79
00:08:10.256 --> 00:08:12.425
Alicent Hightower.

80
00:08:16.395 --> 00:08:20.233
When last we met. Alicent said
I would make a fine queen.

81
00:08:20.733 --> 00:08:22.200
You've seen what has
happened since then.

82
00:08:22.201 --> 00:08:24.769
She came to me in the hours
after your lord father's death.

83
00:08:24.770 --> 00:08:25.904
She knows war is coming.

84
00:08:25.905 --> 00:08:29.108
and that it'll be savage
beyond all compare.

85
00:08:30.042 --> 00:08:35.280
There is no war so hateful to
the gods as a war between kin.

86
00:08:39.118 --> 00:08:43.121
And no war so bloody as
a war between dragons.

87
00:08:43.122 --> 00:08:47.059
- I do not believe she wants it.
- She sent a raven.

88
00:08:48.427 --> 00:08:50.062
I do not care to
read her message.

89
00:08:50.730 --> 00:08:53.965
- What she did...
- It is not her but the men around her who seek bloodshed.

90
00:08:53.966 --> 00:08:55.968
She permitted it.

91
00:08:57.503 --> 00:08:58.803
As you permitted the murder

92
00:08:58.804 --> 00:09:00.405
of a little boy in his bed.

93
00:09:08.614 --> 00:09:13.753
Alicent is in King's Landing.
Her son sits my throne.

94
00:09:15.588 --> 00:09:18.157
There is nothing
more to be said.

95
00:09:32.872 --> 00:09:35.373
Is all well. lord Hand?

96
00:09:37.944 --> 00:09:40.580
Only they'll be waiting.

97
00:10:21.487 --> 00:10:22.787
There have been tidings in...

98
00:10:31.697 --> 00:10:34.967
Good morrow. Your
Grace. My lords.

99
00:10:42.675 --> 00:10:46.378
- Forgive my lateness.
- Important business. no doubt.

100
00:10:46.379 --> 00:10:47.912
You've appointed new knights

101
00:10:47.913 --> 00:10:50.649
- to the Kingsguard. Your Grace.
- To replace those we lost.

102
00:10:50.650 --> 00:10:53.653
The last one needlessly.
some might say.

103
00:10:55.655 --> 00:10:58.957
Ser Arryk was awarded the great
duty of ending Rhaenyra's challenge.

104
00:10:58.958 --> 00:11:00.492
He failed to discharge it.

105
00:11:00.493 --> 00:11:02.027
He failed because
the scheme was rash.

106
00:11:02.028 --> 00:11:04.496
Perhaps. Your Grace. but we
cannot all hide in our castles

107
00:11:04.497 --> 00:11:05.730
waiting for war to come to us.

108
00:11:05.731 --> 00:11:07.298
As now it surely will.

109
00:11:07.299 --> 00:11:09.669
As. now. it already has.

110
00:11:10.403 --> 00:11:13.672
House Bracken took it upon
themselves to attack the Blackwoods.

111
00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:15.874
who declared for the pretender.

112
00:11:15.875 --> 00:11:18.009
Lord Samwell Blackwood
himself is slain.

113
00:11:18.010 --> 00:11:20.780
Good. First blood in our name.

114
00:11:21.180 --> 00:11:23.882
Both sides took heavy
losses. Your Grace.

115
00:11:23.883 --> 00:11:25.750
I-I'm not entirely certain

116
00:11:25.751 --> 00:11:27.485
we can declare this a victory.

117
00:11:27.486 --> 00:11:28.820
The Blackwoods and the Brackens

118
00:11:28.821 --> 00:11:29.988
have feuded for centuries.

119
00:11:29.989 --> 00:11:31.156
This is nothing more

120
00:11:31.157 --> 00:11:32.457
than an excuse for
them to indulge

121
00:11:32.458 --> 00:11:34.627
their ancient grudge.
It's no true war.

122
00:11:36.095 --> 00:11:40.132
Call it what you
will... I call it war.

123
00:11:41.067 --> 00:11:42.301
And so will Dragonstone.

124
00:11:43.035 --> 00:11:47.239
The question is. what are
we going to do about it?

125
00:11:52.611 --> 00:11:55.480
We send a raven to Lord Tully.

126
00:11:55.481 --> 00:11:57.615
These houses are his
vassals. are they not?

127
00:11:57.616 --> 00:12:01.586
- He must control them.
- Lord Grover Tully is a flaccid. old fool

128
00:12:01.587 --> 00:12:04.055
who couldn't control
his cock in a cunny.

129
00:12:04.056 --> 00:12:05.623
Begging your pardon. Your Grace.

130
00:12:05.624 --> 00:12:07.859
Do you have any better
suggestions. Lord Jasper?

131
00:12:07.860 --> 00:12:09.761
Your lord uncle Ormund
marches from Oldtown

132
00:12:09.762 --> 00:12:12.030
at the head of a great
host. Your Grace.

133
00:12:12.031 --> 00:12:14.632
And your brother Daeron's
dragon nears fighting age.

134
00:12:14.633 --> 00:12:16.000
Call on them to
suppress the Riverlands.

135
00:12:16.001 --> 00:12:17.635
Alas. they are months away.

136
00:12:17.636 --> 00:12:18.903
My lord brother Jason

137
00:12:18.904 --> 00:12:20.972
is raising a great
army at Casterly Rock.

138
00:12:20.973 --> 00:12:22.707
In a matter of weeks.
he will be able

139
00:12:22.708 --> 00:12:24.509
to harass the Blackwoods
from the west.

140
00:12:24.510 --> 00:12:26.478
Should we not aim to
unite these armies

141
00:12:26.479 --> 00:12:28.079
and then strike as one?

142
00:12:28.080 --> 00:12:30.782
Ah. the great military
mind of the Citadel.

143
00:12:30.783 --> 00:12:32.584
- I served the realm...
- Do remind me.

144
00:12:32.585 --> 00:12:34.385
which link in your chain
denotes the art of war?

145
00:12:34.386 --> 00:12:36.688
This council must rediscover
the discipline it lately had

146
00:12:36.689 --> 00:12:38.123
if it's to be of any use.

147
00:12:38.124 --> 00:12:40.159
The Riverlands are
the key to the war.

148
00:12:40.893 --> 00:12:43.628
Harrenhal is the key
to the Riverlands.

149
00:12:43.629 --> 00:12:45.330
I will ride out with
those I can muster here.

150
00:12:45.331 --> 00:12:47.265
Men I know. men I've trained.

151
00:12:47.266 --> 00:12:50.368
You need time to raise the
numbers to challenge the Rivermen.

152
00:12:50.369 --> 00:12:51.736
Speed is my ally.

153
00:12:51.737 --> 00:12:53.204
I will turn the Crownland houses

154
00:12:53.205 --> 00:12:54.839
who declared for
Rhaenyra to our cause.

155
00:12:54.840 --> 00:12:58.176
We will add their numbers to
our own and then turn west.

156
00:12:58.177 --> 00:12:59.911
Where I will enlist
the Brackens.

157
00:12:59.912 --> 00:13:03.616
subdue the Riverlands.
and take Harrenhal.

158
00:13:04.216 --> 00:13:06.585
So impatient to ride
with so few men.

159
00:13:06.952 --> 00:13:09.854
So like to be destroyed by
the first stronghold you meet.

160
00:13:09.855 --> 00:13:12.357
- A bold scheme indeed.
- Well. the gods favor the bold.

161
00:13:12.358 --> 00:13:16.127
They did not favor Ser Arryk.

162
00:13:16.128 --> 00:13:18.197
What say you. my king?

163
00:13:19.965 --> 00:13:22.367
And you'll take
Aemond and Vhagar?

164
00:13:22.368 --> 00:13:25.204
Vhagar will remain here...

165
00:13:26.071 --> 00:13:27.306
to defend the city.

166
00:13:28.374 --> 00:13:31.042
Good. To war. then.

167
00:13:31.043 --> 00:13:32.211
Hm.

168
00:13:32.545 --> 00:13:34.045
- I'll come. too. with Sunfyre.
- Aegon.

169
00:13:34.046 --> 00:13:35.780
- Your Grace.
- You'll need a dragon.

170
00:13:35.781 --> 00:13:37.348
My plan is not to
draw attention.

171
00:13:37.349 --> 00:13:40.451
And-And what will you do if
you encounter one or more

172
00:13:40.452 --> 00:13:41.653
of Rhaenyra's dragons?

173
00:13:41.654 --> 00:13:43.087
She'll want to
answer for Ser Arryk.

174
00:13:43.088 --> 00:13:44.789
We will be more like
to encounter one

175
00:13:44.790 --> 00:13:45.958
if we field one of our own.

176
00:13:46.192 --> 00:13:48.993
That is precisely why
you must remain. brother.

177
00:13:48.994 --> 00:13:52.932
It's a brave thought. but
we cannot risk your loss.

178
00:13:56.969 --> 00:13:59.772
I'm as fearsome as any of them.

179
00:14:04.076 --> 00:14:05.176
Oh.

180
00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:28.766
{\an8}I was told you turned back from
your ship to bring warning.

181
00:14:28.767 --> 00:14:31.669
I was not believed at first.

182
00:14:31.670 --> 00:14:33.339
You saved my life.

183
00:14:33.639 --> 00:14:36.774
What is the life of a
queen worth these days?

184
00:14:36.775 --> 00:14:39.377
Hm. you wish to be rewarded.

185
00:14:39.378 --> 00:14:42.180
As. I would think. you
would wish to reward me.

186
00:14:45.317 --> 00:14:46.951
What price would you set?

187
00:14:46.952 --> 00:14:49.488
A place at your court.

188
00:14:53.259 --> 00:14:55.760
You said your earnest
desire was to flee Westeros.

189
00:14:55.761 --> 00:14:57.428
And you let me go.

190
00:14:57.429 --> 00:15:01.634
You showed me grace when
you could have withheld it.

191
00:15:02.635 --> 00:15:04.803
I'm not often surprised.

192
00:15:08.540 --> 00:15:10.876
One turn for another. then.

193
00:15:11.343 --> 00:15:13.611
I know the workings
of the Red Keep.

194
00:15:13.612 --> 00:15:16.781
and the movements of
those who serve there.

195
00:15:16.782 --> 00:15:19.852
That is worth more
than gold to you now.

196
00:15:20.319 --> 00:15:22.121
And what is my worth to you?

197
00:15:25.925 --> 00:15:27.625
I would punish the Hightowers

198
00:15:27.626 --> 00:15:29.327
for what they have done.

199
00:15:29.328 --> 00:15:32.898
To me... to those
who served me.

200
00:15:33.632 --> 00:15:36.034
But more than that.
I know the struggles

201
00:15:36.035 --> 00:15:38.269
of the smallfolk
of King's Landing.

202
00:15:38.270 --> 00:15:42.441
They will be ruled either
by you or by the usurper.

203
00:15:43.142 --> 00:15:46.378
And only one of you has shown
yourself to be merciful.

204
00:15:47.246 --> 00:15:50.716
Well. I hope you do not
confuse mercy with pliancy.

205
00:15:53.819 --> 00:15:55.955
Are they always like this?

206
00:15:56.689 --> 00:15:59.525
Seasmoke. my late
lord husband's dragon.

207
00:16:00.492 --> 00:16:02.393
He's grown restless of late.

208
00:16:02.394 --> 00:16:05.798
- We cannot know why.
- Maybe he's lonely.

209
00:16:14.573 --> 00:16:16.342
Rhaena.

210
00:16:17.409 --> 00:16:18.911
Your Grace.

211
00:16:21.213 --> 00:16:23.614
I've decided to
send Joffrey to ward

212
00:16:23.615 --> 00:16:26.417
with my cousin.
Lady Jeyne Arryn.

213
00:16:26.418 --> 00:16:29.087
She has pledged an army
in return for a dragon.

214
00:16:29.088 --> 00:16:30.055
so she will have one.

215
00:16:30.056 --> 00:16:32.123
Aegon and Viserys
will accompany him

216
00:16:32.124 --> 00:16:34.459
until a place of greater
safety can be found.

217
00:16:34.460 --> 00:16:36.228
Tyraxes is but a hatchling.

218
00:16:36.595 --> 00:16:39.231
- And Stormcloud...
- I want you to go with them.

219
00:16:41.467 --> 00:16:43.401
The Red Keep is in disarray.

220
00:16:43.402 --> 00:16:44.902
They have sent one
assassin in the night

221
00:16:44.903 --> 00:16:47.172
and their dragons are
ever a short flight away.

222
00:16:47.573 --> 00:16:50.908
You must take the little ones
further. To Pentos. I think.

223
00:16:50.909 --> 00:16:52.076
Where my mother died.

224
00:16:52.077 --> 00:16:54.913
It is safer than
anywhere in Westeros.

225
00:16:55.881 --> 00:16:56.914
Write to Prince Reggio.

226
00:16:56.915 --> 00:16:59.885
If he will have
you. then go to him.

227
00:17:00.319 --> 00:17:02.353
I am sorry to put this upon you.

228
00:17:02.354 --> 00:17:04.956
It breaks my heart
to send my boys away.

229
00:17:04.957 --> 00:17:06.424
not knowing when I
will see them again.

230
00:17:06.425 --> 00:17:09.927
But you have seen what
may befall them here.

231
00:17:09.928 --> 00:17:11.263
Rhaena...

232
00:17:12.931 --> 00:17:16.201
I need you to be the mother
to them that I cannot.

233
00:17:17.369 --> 00:17:18.970
Teach them. train them.

234
00:17:18.971 --> 00:17:21.305
guard them as a dragon
guards her eggs.

235
00:17:21.306 --> 00:17:22.708
And my sister?

236
00:17:24.243 --> 00:17:26.277
- I need Baela here.
- Because she has a dragon.

237
00:17:26.278 --> 00:17:28.146
I cannot promise
to make you happy.

238
00:17:28.147 --> 00:17:30.348
But I ask you:

239
00:17:30.349 --> 00:17:32.884
make this sacrifice willingly.

240
00:17:32.885 --> 00:17:34.153
for all of us.

241
00:17:35.988 --> 00:17:37.289
Your Grace.

242
00:18:14.927 --> 00:18:16.761
Dragon!

243
00:20:50.682 --> 00:20:51.950
Halt!

244
00:21:05.764 --> 00:21:07.666
I'm claiming Harrenhal.

245
00:21:10.335 --> 00:21:12.037
Apparently so.

246
00:21:33.225 --> 00:21:36.427
I. Ser Simon Strong.
Castellan of Harrenhal.

247
00:21:36.428 --> 00:21:39.430
pledge fealty to Rhaenyra
of House Targaryen.

248
00:21:39.431 --> 00:21:41.299
First of Her Name.

249
00:21:41.300 --> 00:21:44.202
I swear this by the
old gods and the new.

250
00:21:45.771 --> 00:21:49.707
Supper is venison with
black cabbage and peas.

251
00:21:49.708 --> 00:21:53.578
No redcurrant.
Sorry about that.

252
00:22:01.853 --> 00:22:04.222
That venison is well aged.

253
00:22:05.357 --> 00:22:06.925
Shame to let it waste.

254
00:22:10.696 --> 00:22:11.996
I've survived many a battle.

255
00:22:11.997 --> 00:22:14.732
I do not mean to be
felled by poisoned peas.

256
00:22:14.733 --> 00:22:17.568
I'll admit that my cook's peas

257
00:22:17.569 --> 00:22:20.938
aren't exactly the stuff
of legend. but poison?

258
00:22:20.939 --> 00:22:24.343
Well. it's an easy way
to kill a dragonrider.

259
00:22:25.744 --> 00:22:29.081
If you've not yet surmised.
you are welcome here.

260
00:22:29.448 --> 00:22:33.819
And what of your lord.
Larys Strong. hm?

261
00:22:34.453 --> 00:22:36.654
He who sits at the
false court of Aegon?

262
00:22:36.655 --> 00:22:40.125
Larys Clubfoot is
no lord of mine.

263
00:22:41.026 --> 00:22:44.663
He is a scourge upon this
castle and this family.

264
00:22:45.497 --> 00:22:48.734
Do you not think it's
strange that his father...

265
00:22:50.635 --> 00:22:54.405
my nephew. Lord Lyonel.
perished by fire?

266
00:22:54.406 --> 00:22:59.111
And his son. too. here
in this damp place?

267
00:23:00.545 --> 00:23:02.580
It was the first fire
here since Balerion ended

268
00:23:02.581 --> 00:23:04.015
the line of Harren the Black.

269
00:23:04.649 --> 00:23:06.617
Even in the summer. we
struggle to light the hearths.

270
00:23:06.618 --> 00:23:10.354
So. no. you will find no loyalty
to Larys Strong here. my prince.

271
00:23:10.355 --> 00:23:11.623
"Your Grace."

272
00:23:16.895 --> 00:23:18.897
Forgive me. I-I. um...

273
00:23:20.532 --> 00:23:23.434
I... I'd only assumed
that as consort...

274
00:23:23.435 --> 00:23:26.304
Then we are reminded of the
perilousness of assumption.

275
00:23:27.873 --> 00:23:29.141
Indeed.

276
00:23:31.943 --> 00:23:33.445
Your Grace.

277
00:23:38.183 --> 00:23:41.519
What then brings you to our
corner of the Riverlands?

278
00:23:41.520 --> 00:23:44.856
Harrenhal is the largest
castle in the Seven Kingdoms.

279
00:23:45.690 --> 00:23:47.691
Or perhaps that has
escaped your attention.

280
00:23:47.692 --> 00:23:49.727
But it is also. not
to be argumentative.

281
00:23:49.728 --> 00:23:51.595
in something of a
state of disrepair

282
00:23:51.596 --> 00:23:55.065
since your forbear incinerated
much of it with his dragon.

283
00:23:55.066 --> 00:23:59.470
Well. that is precisely why we must
bring it into a state of repair.

284
00:23:59.471 --> 00:24:02.841
Even if we possessed
the coin. my prin...

285
00:24:04.109 --> 00:24:06.310
Your Grace. to
what possible end?

286
00:24:06.311 --> 00:24:08.446
There are 40.000 swords
in the Riverlands.

287
00:24:08.447 --> 00:24:10.347
the largest undeclared
host in the realm.

288
00:24:10.348 --> 00:24:13.117
Only Harrenhal is of a size
enough to garrison them.

289
00:24:13.118 --> 00:24:14.585
You should know that
a substantial number

290
00:24:14.586 --> 00:24:16.454
of those swords
have now declared

291
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.088
and are presently at war.

292
00:24:18.089 --> 00:24:21.592
Houses Bracken and Blackwood
have long detested one another.

293
00:24:21.593 --> 00:24:23.995
- Why?
- Oh. well...

294
00:24:25.464 --> 00:24:30.068
the answer to that
is... lost in time.

295
00:24:30.969 --> 00:24:34.739
Sin begets sin begets sin.

296
00:24:37.476 --> 00:24:38.609
Summon your lord paramount

297
00:24:38.610 --> 00:24:40.277
so that I may treat
with him myself

298
00:24:40.278 --> 00:24:41.812
and turn them to our cause.

299
00:24:41.813 --> 00:24:45.349
That would be Lord Grover
Tully. but he grows frail.

300
00:24:45.350 --> 00:24:47.853
It's said that he can
no longer speak...

301
00:24:49.087 --> 00:24:51.089
nor seal his bowels.

302
00:24:51.423 --> 00:24:53.157
Begging your pardon
for the impression.

303
00:24:53.158 --> 00:24:54.792
His grip on his
bannermen is weak.

304
00:24:54.793 --> 00:24:56.093
They feel they can
do as they please.

305
00:24:56.094 --> 00:24:57.828
I will speak with
him nonetheless.

306
00:24:57.829 --> 00:25:00.332
People should obey
their liege lord...

307
00:25:01.132 --> 00:25:03.801
whatever his condition.

308
00:25:03.802 --> 00:25:06.071
Perhaps the presence
of the crown

309
00:25:07.105 --> 00:25:08.707
and a dragon

310
00:25:09.140 --> 00:25:12.010
will sharpen minds
around these parts.

311
00:25:13.245 --> 00:25:15.614
Might I ask. Your Grace...

312
00:25:16.515 --> 00:25:17.615
if you are successful.

313
00:25:17.616 --> 00:25:20.150
w-well. when you
are successful...

314
00:25:20.151 --> 00:25:22.486
what then?

315
00:25:22.487 --> 00:25:25.423
We march on King's Landing
and take the throne.

316
00:25:27.425 --> 00:25:29.060
The throne.

317
00:25:32.130 --> 00:25:36.101
It's a big chair made of swords.

318
00:25:37.035 --> 00:25:40.704
Standard-bearers to the front!

319
00:25:40.705 --> 00:25:43.241
Packhorses to the rear!

320
00:25:43.742 --> 00:25:46.410
Clear way for the
mounted knights...

321
00:25:57.422 --> 00:26:01.325
Lord Commander. Your host is
mustered and ready to march.

322
00:26:01.326 --> 00:26:03.694
He enjoys battle.

323
00:26:08.033 --> 00:26:10.200
I'm glad we're
together. even briefly.

324
00:26:10.201 --> 00:26:12.770
Ser Criston.

325
00:26:12.771 --> 00:26:15.806
May I present my brother.
Ser Gwayne Hightower.

326
00:26:15.807 --> 00:26:17.908
arrived last night from Oldtown.

327
00:26:17.909 --> 00:26:19.244
Ser Criston.

328
00:26:20.111 --> 00:26:23.882
Or mayhaps I should
say. my lord Hand?

329
00:26:24.316 --> 00:26:26.451
Ser Gwayne. welcome
to King's Landing.

330
00:26:26.985 --> 00:26:30.187
How exhilarating to
arrive at court after

331
00:26:30.188 --> 00:26:31.956
three long months on the road

332
00:26:31.957 --> 00:26:34.258
to find my lord father.

333
00:26:34.259 --> 00:26:36.527
who served three
kings faithfully.

334
00:26:36.528 --> 00:26:38.296
unseated as Hand of the King.

335
00:26:40.332 --> 00:26:43.834
And by a man from such
modest beginnings.

336
00:26:43.835 --> 00:26:44.835
Hm.

337
00:26:45.270 --> 00:26:49.773
What a giddying ascent the
gods have bestowed on you.

338
00:26:49.774 --> 00:26:53.011
Ser Gwayne has volunteered
to accompany you into battle.

339
00:26:56.982 --> 00:26:58.882
We have a full
complement. Your Grace.

340
00:26:58.883 --> 00:27:01.186
Then you shall
have a fuller one.

341
00:27:02.854 --> 00:27:04.623
The march will be hard. Ser.

342
00:27:05.123 --> 00:27:07.124
No one is more delighted than I

343
00:27:07.125 --> 00:27:09.194
to march out to war
with a Dornishman.

344
00:27:10.795 --> 00:27:11.863
Sister.

345
00:27:19.804 --> 00:27:23.107
May the Seven guide
you. good knight...

346
00:27:23.108 --> 00:27:25.710
and lead you not into
shadow and death.

347
00:27:27.579 --> 00:27:29.514
I thank Your Grace
for her prayers.

348
00:27:33.184 --> 00:27:35.754
And request that she
grant her favor...

349
00:27:36.821 --> 00:27:39.758
that her Lord Commander may go
into battle with her blessings

350
00:27:41.159 --> 00:27:42.894
in his heart.

351
00:27:54.706 --> 00:27:56.007
Your Grace.

352
00:28:07.519 --> 00:28:09.220
Hyah!

353
00:28:45.924 --> 00:28:48.926
Still no sightings.

354
00:28:48.927 --> 00:28:53.798
No men. no horses. no ships.

355
00:28:55.767 --> 00:28:57.568
- No dragons.
- Good.

356
00:28:57.569 --> 00:29:02.206
Then we must seize the hour
and act before our enemy does.

357
00:29:02.207 --> 00:29:03.607
They have penetrated
our castle walls.

358
00:29:03.608 --> 00:29:05.142
and now the
Riverlands are aflame

359
00:29:05.143 --> 00:29:07.278
after the Battle at
the Burning Mill.

360
00:29:07.746 --> 00:29:10.615
How fares Prince
Daemon with our army?

361
00:29:11.549 --> 00:29:14.752
There has been no word from
Prince Daemon. Your Grace.

362
00:29:14.753 --> 00:29:17.554
Then we must press what
advantage we do have.

363
00:29:17.555 --> 00:29:20.891
- And what is that?
- Dragons. Send them all out.

364
00:29:20.892 --> 00:29:24.795
Start turning Green
strongholds to our cause

365
00:29:24.796 --> 00:29:27.365
- and burn those who resist.
- No.

366
00:29:27.999 --> 00:29:29.933
If dragons begin
fighting dragons.

367
00:29:29.934 --> 00:29:32.669
we invite our own destruction.

368
00:29:32.670 --> 00:29:34.973
Fear of it is in
itself a weapon.

369
00:29:35.540 --> 00:29:38.843
The Greens will make
the same calculation.

370
00:29:40.211 --> 00:29:44.048
The value of a sword is
not within its scabbard.

371
00:29:44.516 --> 00:29:47.151
We will secure
victory with armies.

372
00:29:47.152 --> 00:29:49.354
not with dragons alone.

373
00:29:50.488 --> 00:29:51.990
The Greens understand that.

374
00:29:52.390 --> 00:29:54.859
The Vale and the
North will send men.

375
00:29:56.094 --> 00:29:58.329
We must give Daemon time.

376
00:29:58.797 --> 00:30:02.466
Ah. Your Grace. you have
witnessed firsthand just how

377
00:30:02.467 --> 00:30:04.234
vulnerable you are.

378
00:30:04.235 --> 00:30:06.203
Prince Daemon is abroad.

379
00:30:06.204 --> 00:30:09.339
and Aegon's factions are
enraged at the death of his son.

380
00:30:09.340 --> 00:30:11.475
You have never been so exposed.

381
00:30:11.476 --> 00:30:13.577
Perhaps it is time
for you to think about

382
00:30:13.578 --> 00:30:16.180
secreting yourself
somewhere safe.

383
00:30:16.181 --> 00:30:17.447
while we remain here

384
00:30:17.448 --> 00:30:21.451
as a source of
distraction for the enemy.

385
00:30:21.452 --> 00:30:23.353
You propose to conduct
the war in my absence.

386
00:30:23.354 --> 00:30:27.058
- It would merely be a precaution...
- It would be treason.

387
00:30:30.228 --> 00:30:32.697
You are fortunate you
took it no further.

388
00:30:40.371 --> 00:30:41.972
This council would
do well to remember

389
00:30:41.973 --> 00:30:44.708
that their queen wears
the crown of my grandsire.

390
00:30:44.709 --> 00:30:47.111
Jaehaerys the Conciliator.

391
00:30:47.512 --> 00:30:50.681
A prudent ruler. the
wisest of Targaryen kings.

392
00:30:50.682 --> 00:30:53.384
whose reign outlasted
every other...

393
00:30:55.486 --> 00:30:57.856
even Aegon the Conqueror's.

394
00:31:03.428 --> 00:31:05.362
So. how do they fare?

395
00:31:05.363 --> 00:31:07.297
The ditherers of Dragonstone?

396
00:31:07.298 --> 00:31:11.468
Rhaenyra's council is
wayward. She has a hard task.

397
00:31:11.469 --> 00:31:13.737
I must hope she will rise to it.

398
00:31:13.738 --> 00:31:17.307
but I fear she'll need you
by her side sooner than late.

399
00:31:17.308 --> 00:31:19.477
This bread. still warm.

400
00:31:20.111 --> 00:31:22.313
There's broth too.
I made sure of it.

401
00:31:23.615 --> 00:31:25.783
I am no longer an invalid.

402
00:31:32.423 --> 00:31:35.660
I bade farewell to
Rhaena before I returned.

403
00:31:38.997 --> 00:31:40.765
I wish her well.

404
00:31:42.333 --> 00:31:44.835
I would fight a hundred battles
before I went into exile

405
00:31:44.836 --> 00:31:47.105
with none but prattling babes.

406
00:31:48.339 --> 00:31:50.707
One of those babes is your heir.

407
00:31:50.708 --> 00:31:52.610
Joffrey.

408
00:31:53.144 --> 00:31:56.647
A boy of six who knows
nothing of the sea

409
00:31:56.648 --> 00:31:58.349
and yet somehow...

410
00:31:58.816 --> 00:32:01.818
It would displease neither
Rhaenyra nor the gods

411
00:32:01.819 --> 00:32:05.823
if Rhaena were named
heir to Driftmark.

412
00:32:07.959 --> 00:32:10.995
Rhaena? Lord of the Tides?

413
00:32:11.496 --> 00:32:14.364
The girl knows nothing of
ships. nor even of dragons.

414
00:32:14.365 --> 00:32:16.868
There is Rhaena or
there is Joffrey.

415
00:32:17.435 --> 00:32:21.773
Both soon to be far from the creak
of ships and the ocean's roar.

416
00:32:23.141 --> 00:32:27.245
Then we must hope to...

417
00:32:27.745 --> 00:32:30.047
see our way forward. in time.

418
00:32:30.048 --> 00:32:32.483
And if there is no time?

419
00:32:34.886 --> 00:32:37.221
We are at war. Corlys.

420
00:32:38.823 --> 00:32:43.794
- If something were to befall you...
- Then... it is well

421
00:32:43.795 --> 00:32:45.863
that I am a good sailor.

422
00:32:59.510 --> 00:33:01.378
I have much to attend to.

423
00:33:01.379 --> 00:33:03.013
Corlys. Corl...

424
00:33:26.537 --> 00:33:28.739
I cannot spare a
fighting dragon.

425
00:33:28.740 --> 00:33:30.107
but I send what I can.

426
00:33:30.108 --> 00:33:32.409
Stormcloud and
Tyraxes are small.

427
00:33:32.410 --> 00:33:35.078
but they will grow.

428
00:33:35.079 --> 00:33:38.015
It is for you to remind
Lady Jeyne of her pledge

429
00:33:38.016 --> 00:33:41.953
and persuade her of the
urgency of our need.

430
00:33:48.359 --> 00:33:50.695
Go safely. sister.

431
00:33:51.996 --> 00:33:54.264
I will be safe enough.

432
00:33:54.265 --> 00:33:56.099
Far away from any danger.

433
00:33:56.100 --> 00:33:57.901
with only babes to nursemaid.

434
00:33:57.902 --> 00:34:00.003
You do a great service.

435
00:34:00.004 --> 00:34:02.005
and may yet find yourself
glad to be out of harm's way.

436
00:34:02.006 --> 00:34:04.174
Do not coddle me. Baela.

437
00:34:04.175 --> 00:34:06.910
- Grant me at least that dignity.
- I meant no insult.

438
00:34:06.911 --> 00:34:09.112
We each do what we can.

439
00:34:09.113 --> 00:34:12.216
And here. I think.
is some consolation.

440
00:34:14.619 --> 00:34:17.889
Tyraxes and Stormcloud
are young and vulnerable.

441
00:34:18.823 --> 00:34:22.093
These eggs are
even more fragile.

442
00:34:23.161 --> 00:34:26.397
But should all come
to ruin here...

443
00:34:27.432 --> 00:34:29.634
you will bear our
hope for the future.

444
00:34:32.170 --> 00:34:33.271
Your Grace.

445
00:34:34.072 --> 00:34:36.240
Mommy.

446
00:36:11.402 --> 00:36:12.937
My Queen.

447
00:36:15.173 --> 00:36:18.341
I feel sad about Jaehaerys.

448
00:36:18.342 --> 00:36:21.212
Mm. but I ought not to. I think.

449
00:36:22.013 --> 00:36:24.347
People die all the time.

450
00:36:24.348 --> 00:36:26.250
especially babes.

451
00:36:26.784 --> 00:36:30.888
They're so little. s-so
they're taken so easily.

452
00:36:34.125 --> 00:36:37.027
Sadness is a condition
of motherhood.

453
00:36:37.028 --> 00:36:39.530
There's naught to
be gained from it.

454
00:36:43.935 --> 00:36:47.404
That horrid procession where
the smallfolk all stared at me.

455
00:36:47.405 --> 00:36:51.809
I warrant they thought I had no
more right to grief than they do.

456
00:36:54.078 --> 00:36:57.782
Surely they lose their babes
more than highborn ladies.

457
00:37:01.819 --> 00:37:03.988
The Stranger comes for us all...

458
00:37:05.056 --> 00:37:06.791
queen and commoner.

459
00:37:08.593 --> 00:37:11.262
You have as much claim
to grief as anyone.

460
00:37:13.497 --> 00:37:14.765
And you?

461
00:37:19.170 --> 00:37:20.971
I loved Jaehaerys. but
my concern has been

462
00:37:20.972 --> 00:37:23.674
more for you and what
you have endured.

463
00:37:25.543 --> 00:37:29.146
- Uh. Helaena. I...
- I forgive you.

464
00:37:30.715 --> 00:37:31.949
What?

465
00:37:36.921 --> 00:37:39.090
I said that I forgive you.

466
00:37:44.495 --> 00:37:46.998
Suits you. Your Grace.

467
00:37:47.431 --> 00:37:50.700
Valyrian steel. Worth
more than a castle.

468
00:37:50.701 --> 00:37:53.170
A sight to stir the passions.

469
00:37:53.638 --> 00:37:55.705
Aegon the Conqueror reborn.

470
00:37:55.706 --> 00:37:57.007
Just get on with it.

471
00:37:57.008 --> 00:37:58.508
At once. Your Grace.

472
00:37:58.509 --> 00:38:00.143
What is your business?

473
00:38:00.144 --> 00:38:03.381
There are rumors that the King
readies himself to fly to war.

474
00:38:03.914 --> 00:38:05.783
And what is it to you?

475
00:38:06.284 --> 00:38:07.817
Only that I think it
would benefit all of us

476
00:38:07.818 --> 00:38:11.288
to prevent our king from being
brutally slain by our enemies.

477
00:38:11.289 --> 00:38:13.690
and his body parts
scattered to beasts.

478
00:38:13.691 --> 00:38:14.958
and his court come to ruin.

479
00:38:14.959 --> 00:38:16.560
Would you not agree?

480
00:38:19.397 --> 00:38:21.365
What exquisite armor.

481
00:38:24.135 --> 00:38:27.203
I was given the Conqueror's
name and his crown.

482
00:38:27.204 --> 00:38:29.506
so I shall wear
his armor to war.

483
00:38:29.507 --> 00:38:32.876
I fly to meet Ser Criston.

484
00:38:32.877 --> 00:38:36.047
Small imposition before you
depart then. Your Grace.

485
00:38:46.757 --> 00:38:50.360
There are diverse rumors whispered
on the streets of your city.

486
00:38:50.361 --> 00:38:53.863
One such is that Your Grace
sends his forces to battle.

487
00:38:53.864 --> 00:38:55.398
and. in his courage and wisdom.

488
00:38:55.399 --> 00:38:57.201
flies with them.

489
00:38:59.270 --> 00:39:02.839
Another is that His Grace was
outwitted by his counselors

490
00:39:02.840 --> 00:39:05.942
and persuaded to fly to
war with Ser Criston.

491
00:39:05.943 --> 00:39:07.977
so that Queen Alicent

492
00:39:07.978 --> 00:39:10.381
may reign in his absence

493
00:39:10.981 --> 00:39:13.718
with Prince Aemond at her side.

494
00:39:15.119 --> 00:39:16.854
Absurd. of course.

495
00:39:18.489 --> 00:39:21.692
Who spreads these lies?

496
00:39:22.393 --> 00:39:24.028
It matters little.

497
00:39:24.462 --> 00:39:26.897
Tales take on a
life of their own...

498
00:39:27.631 --> 00:39:28.899
like weeds.

499
00:39:29.333 --> 00:39:31.469
Unless they are tended.

500
00:39:32.470 --> 00:39:34.372
Well. tend to them then.

501
00:39:42.747 --> 00:39:44.081
Lord Larys.

502
00:39:46.016 --> 00:39:48.418
My father always
said he had no use

503
00:39:48.419 --> 00:39:50.554
for a master of whisperers.

504
00:39:51.822 --> 00:39:56.260
And yet... I find
myself wanting for one.

505
00:39:57.762 --> 00:40:00.398
I should be glad
of your talents.

506
00:40:04.435 --> 00:40:06.604
You honor me. Your Grace.

507
00:40:12.676 --> 00:40:16.013
Shall we escort you to
the Dragonpit. Your Grace?

508
00:40:19.083 --> 00:40:20.151
Uh...

509
00:40:22.620 --> 00:40:24.821
I think. mayhaps. I
shall fly another day.

510
00:40:24.822 --> 00:40:28.391
Yeah. it-it does seem
wise on reflection.

511
00:40:28.392 --> 00:40:30.593
You could come out
with us. my king.

512
00:40:30.594 --> 00:40:33.230
Ser Martyn has a new squire
that wants bedding in.

513
00:40:33.631 --> 00:40:36.033
He's never fucked a woman.

514
00:40:36.434 --> 00:40:39.537
But you are sworn
to chastity now.

515
00:40:41.472 --> 00:40:44.108
Of course. Your Grace.

516
00:40:49.547 --> 00:40:51.282
Yes. Your Grace.

517
00:40:53.951 --> 00:40:55.019
Hm.

518
00:41:28.018 --> 00:41:30.186
No. no. no. no. no. no.
Don't tell me you're going.

519
00:41:30.187 --> 00:41:32.455
- I'm not going yet.
- I've only just got here.

520
00:41:36.427 --> 00:41:37.560
There he is!

521
00:41:39.396 --> 00:41:42.233
Ulf. Ulf. come on. son!

522
00:41:43.868 --> 00:41:46.035
It turns out. it was her sister.

523
00:41:46.036 --> 00:41:48.037
Probably should've told me.

524
00:41:48.038 --> 00:41:50.874
I know. I know. I know!

525
00:41:50.875 --> 00:41:53.176
Take that one. You'll get your
pound of flesh. don't worry.

526
00:41:53.177 --> 00:41:54.811
Sit yourself down. mate.

527
00:41:54.812 --> 00:41:56.980
- Hello.
- I've been tellin' this fella all about you.

528
00:41:56.981 --> 00:41:58.915
Oh. lads.

529
00:41:58.916 --> 00:42:01.084
- I've had quite a day of it.
- Yeah?

530
00:42:01.085 --> 00:42:03.187
Not sure I'm much for talkin'.

531
00:42:03.988 --> 00:42:07.625
Although. you know. a wet
whistle works wonders.

532
00:42:08.492 --> 00:42:09.560
Hm.

533
00:42:12.296 --> 00:42:15.131
Come on. Ulf. give us a
flagon over there. yeah?

534
00:42:15.132 --> 00:42:18.501
Yeah. my darling. one for
the flagon. one for yourself.

535
00:42:18.502 --> 00:42:20.637
There's a good girl. eh?

536
00:42:24.675 --> 00:42:26.376
No sense of fun. some of 'em.

537
00:42:26.377 --> 00:42:30.047
- For you. man of Dorne.
- Dornish. are ya?

538
00:42:30.915 --> 00:42:34.817
- Yes. I am.
- The part of Westeros my house never settled.

539
00:42:34.818 --> 00:42:36.152
Although. it's said even Dorne

540
00:42:36.153 --> 00:42:38.989
mourned the passing of
my grandsire. Is that so?

541
00:42:39.456 --> 00:42:41.225
Who was your grandsire?

542
00:42:44.728 --> 00:42:48.197
They call him the Conciliator.

543
00:42:48.198 --> 00:42:50.601
- King Jaehaerys?
- Shh!

544
00:42:51.969 --> 00:42:55.271
Thousand apologies.
Please. continue.

545
00:42:55.272 --> 00:42:58.242
Look. I-I really shouldn't
be telling you this.

546
00:42:59.009 --> 00:43:00.343
You'll cost me my head.

547
00:43:00.344 --> 00:43:03.314
- You are saying you're a Targaryen?
- Shh-shh-shh.

548
00:43:08.052 --> 00:43:11.422
I'm the son of Baelon the Brave.

549
00:43:12.056 --> 00:43:15.024
Bastard brother to Prince Daemon

550
00:43:15.025 --> 00:43:16.893
and the late King Viserys.

551
00:43:16.894 --> 00:43:22.366
Uncle to the one true
queen. Rhaenyra Targaryen.

552
00:43:23.167 --> 00:43:25.935
The blood of the dragon
runs through these veins.

553
00:43:25.936 --> 00:43:29.607
And. yes... men would
take my head for it.

554
00:43:32.209 --> 00:43:34.277
A Dragonseed must
watch his own neck

555
00:43:34.278 --> 00:43:38.282
when he has no white-cloaked
guardsmen to do it for him.

556
00:43:39.950 --> 00:43:42.486
You do not look very
much like King Viserys

557
00:43:43.420 --> 00:43:45.022
or Prince Daemon.

558
00:43:47.157 --> 00:43:48.958
How do you know
what they look like?

559
00:43:48.959 --> 00:43:50.893
He speaks truth. right enough.

560
00:43:50.894 --> 00:43:54.330
Look. you can
tell... by his hair.

561
00:43:54.331 --> 00:43:57.734
Yeah. 'cause I'm their
half-brother. you fuckwit.

562
00:43:57.735 --> 00:44:00.303
Yeah. I'll tell you who else
doesn't have silver hair.

563
00:44:00.304 --> 00:44:02.071
The rightful heir
to the Iron Throne.

564
00:44:02.072 --> 00:44:05.008
my nephew. Prince
Jacaerys Velaryon.

565
00:44:09.079 --> 00:44:10.848
Here's your other nephew.

566
00:44:17.888 --> 00:44:22.725
- All hail the King!
- All hail the King!

567
00:44:22.726 --> 00:44:26.529
Drinks for all! At the
pleasure of the crown!

568
00:44:28.599 --> 00:44:33.570
Woo! At the pleasure
of the crown!

569
00:44:34.738 --> 00:44:36.739
Sit down. Sit yourself down.

570
00:44:36.740 --> 00:44:38.908
- Sit!
- Drink the wine. boy.

571
00:44:38.909 --> 00:44:41.077
- Come on. then!
- Drink up. little piggy!

572
00:44:41.078 --> 00:44:44.514
This night is for you.

573
00:44:44.515 --> 00:44:46.583
You!

574
00:44:54.124 --> 00:44:57.660
Did I. did I tell you
I came here as a lad?

575
00:44:57.661 --> 00:45:00.196
It's. mm. a little tame.

576
00:45:00.197 --> 00:45:03.099
but a good a place
as any to get it wet.

577
00:45:03.100 --> 00:45:07.271
I know just the tutor
for you. my boy.

578
00:45:10.407 --> 00:45:11.441
No.

579
00:45:11.442 --> 00:45:13.509
She's worth three
times the price.

580
00:45:16.080 --> 00:45:19.849
- Oh. gods be good.
- That's you!

581
00:45:19.850 --> 00:45:22.185
Her name is. uh. Sylvi

582
00:45:22.186 --> 00:45:26.222
or Selyse or. I don't
know. something like that.

583
00:45:35.265 --> 00:45:36.799
Aemond. the fierce!

584
00:45:36.800 --> 00:45:40.069
You have come so far.

585
00:45:40.070 --> 00:45:43.473
and. and yet you still
lie with your very first.

586
00:45:44.608 --> 00:45:47.710
What a fine. sweet thing.

587
00:45:49.246 --> 00:45:51.347
Did you fuck her like a hound?

588
00:45:55.452 --> 00:45:57.653
You see. I do not exaggerate.

589
00:45:57.654 --> 00:45:59.655
Such is the madam's prowess.

590
00:45:59.656 --> 00:46:03.526
that even now my brother
will not sample another.

591
00:46:06.096 --> 00:46:07.930
Hard luck for your
squire. though.

592
00:46:07.931 --> 00:46:09.966
As you can see. she...

593
00:46:09.967 --> 00:46:12.468
she's now very much occupied.

594
00:46:21.044 --> 00:46:23.112
Your squire is welcome to her.

595
00:46:24.648 --> 00:46:26.582
One whore is as good as another.

596
00:46:34.625 --> 00:46:36.193
Ah...

597
00:47:43.827 --> 00:47:47.030
{\an8}Criston: Ser Gwayne! Halt!

598
00:47:52.069 --> 00:47:55.572
- Ser Gwayne. our company is camped back yonder.
- Mm.

599
00:47:55.973 --> 00:47:58.174
On the cold. hard ground.

600
00:47:58.175 --> 00:48:00.443
Which is why we
make for the Bull.

601
00:48:00.444 --> 00:48:02.245
a tavern with an
excellent reputation

602
00:48:02.246 --> 00:48:03.880
on the Rosby Road.
not two miles away.

603
00:48:03.881 --> 00:48:06.148
- if memory serves.
- We march to make the first strike

604
00:48:06.149 --> 00:48:07.417
in the name of His Grace.

605
00:48:08.151 --> 00:48:12.456
I assure you. my nephew will not
begrudge me a night of comfort.

606
00:48:17.928 --> 00:48:20.129
If it soothes your brow. Cole.

607
00:48:20.130 --> 00:48:23.267
we will rendezvous with
your army at first light.

608
00:48:23.667 --> 00:48:24.700
Or. if their wine is good.

609
00:48:24.701 --> 00:48:26.937
perhaps a little
after first light.

610
00:48:29.373 --> 00:48:31.575
- We're exposed.
- What?

611
00:48:33.277 --> 00:48:37.079
- Cole?
- Get to the trees!

612
00:48:37.080 --> 00:48:39.583
Hyah! Hyah!

613
00:49:07.744 --> 00:49:09.947
Hah! Hyah!

614
00:50:34.664 --> 00:50:36.800
A good showing. Ser Criston.

615
00:50:39.736 --> 00:50:43.606
- I am in your debt.
- They know we're abroad. They'll be hunting.

616
00:50:43.607 --> 00:50:44.807
And we must move under the trees

617
00:50:44.808 --> 00:50:47.310
and by cover of dark.
starting tonight.

618
00:50:48.278 --> 00:50:50.614
And no fucking inns.

619
00:50:53.617 --> 00:50:55.652
Ser Criston Cole...

620
00:50:56.119 --> 00:50:58.988
with some half-dozen other
knights. I'm sure of it.

621
00:50:58.989 --> 00:51:01.057
Perhaps a scout party
for a greater army.

622
00:51:01.058 --> 00:51:03.259
Maester Gerardys: The ravens
confirm it. Your Grace.

623
00:51:03.260 --> 00:51:06.195
Lord Farring has
reported a larger force

624
00:51:06.196 --> 00:51:09.565
moving northeast towards Rosby.

625
00:51:09.566 --> 00:51:12.368
Could you be certain it was
Cole from such a great height?

626
00:51:12.369 --> 00:51:15.105
It was not such a great
height. Your Grace.

627
00:51:17.240 --> 00:51:20.543
You said not to engage.
so I didn't. exactly.

628
00:51:20.544 --> 00:51:24.847
Your Grace. we commend the
Lady Baela for her sharp eyes.

629
00:51:24.848 --> 00:51:26.348
but we can tarry no longer.

630
00:51:26.349 --> 00:51:28.651
The time for action
is surely now.

631
00:51:28.652 --> 00:51:30.219
Your Grace. I must agree

632
00:51:30.220 --> 00:51:31.387
and request your permission

633
00:51:31.388 --> 00:51:34.056
to return to Rook's Rest
and fortify my lands.

634
00:51:34.057 --> 00:51:35.724
I shouldn't fret. Lord Simon.

635
00:51:35.725 --> 00:51:37.493
They'll be making for Harrenhal.

636
00:51:37.494 --> 00:51:39.462
'Tis Prince Daemon
who ought to worry.

637
00:51:39.463 --> 00:51:40.930
Prince Daemon has Caraxes.

638
00:51:40.931 --> 00:51:43.099
Cole will look to
increase his numbers.

639
00:51:43.100 --> 00:51:45.134
and he may call upon
a dragon of his own.

640
00:51:45.135 --> 00:51:48.938
This is why you must
act now. Your Grace.

641
00:51:48.939 --> 00:51:51.740
Loose the dragons. Root
Cole out and burn him.

642
00:52:07.757 --> 00:52:09.893
I have heard your arguments.

643
00:52:11.394 --> 00:52:13.929
And will consider them.

644
00:54:12.249 --> 00:54:15.652
Always coming and
going. aren't you?

645
00:54:21.391 --> 00:54:24.628
And I have to clean
up afterwards.

646
00:55:05.201 --> 00:55:07.304
You will die in this place.

647
00:55:26.156 --> 00:55:29.191
Elinda Massey: my youngest brother.
Emmon. would stand at guard

648
00:55:29.192 --> 00:55:31.260
with the soldiers when
he was three years old.

649
00:55:31.261 --> 00:55:32.594
Father has sent
him to the Citadel.

650
00:55:32.595 --> 00:55:35.365
- Now. if you ask me...
- Thank you. Elinda.

651
00:55:35.899 --> 00:55:37.200
Your Grace.

652
00:55:44.307 --> 00:55:47.610
What do you know of the
movements of Alicent Hightower?

653
00:55:50.914 --> 00:55:53.883
W-Would you take her hostage?

654
00:55:54.284 --> 00:55:56.318
Or kill her outright?

655
00:55:56.319 --> 00:56:00.189
I would speak with her. myself.

656
00:56:00.190 --> 00:56:02.759
Killing her would be easier.

657
00:56:03.927 --> 00:56:07.230
If war can be averted. it
is my duty to avert it.

658
00:56:07.831 --> 00:56:10.700
I have reason to believe she
may be of the same opinion.

659
00:56:11.401 --> 00:56:14.636
She sent a raven. She has
expressed her remorse.

660
00:56:14.637 --> 00:56:16.305
I can have a message
brought to her.

661
00:56:16.306 --> 00:56:19.007
- in secret.
- She would not agree to it.

662
00:56:19.008 --> 00:56:22.444
She would suspect
some subterfuge.

663
00:56:22.445 --> 00:56:24.913
as would I. if I
received such a message.

664
00:56:24.914 --> 00:56:28.418
I must see her face to face.

665
00:56:31.654 --> 00:56:33.422
She is the queen dowager.

666
00:56:33.423 --> 00:56:36.760
She goes nowhere without
many eyes watching her.

667
00:56:38.661 --> 00:56:41.798
Unless...

668
00:56:45.802 --> 00:56:49.071
- 'Tis fraught.
- Speak it.

669
00:56:49.072 --> 00:56:53.609
There are fishing boats
aplenty in the bay.

670
00:56:53.610 --> 00:56:55.210
The city depends on them.

671
00:56:55.211 --> 00:56:57.679
Daemon made the
journey unhindered.

672
00:56:57.680 --> 00:57:00.783
- But if I'm recognized...
- You may be surprised to learn it.

673
00:57:00.784 --> 00:57:04.820
but most folk pay no mind to a woman
who has not dressed as a queen.

674
00:57:04.821 --> 00:57:08.091
or allured herself
for the eyes of men.

675
00:57:11.060 --> 00:57:14.530
So. I make my way to
the Red Keep. I presume.

676
00:57:14.531 --> 00:57:16.899
and ring the bell.

677
00:57:16.900 --> 00:57:19.601
Or do I scale the wall
and enter at her window?

678
00:57:19.602 --> 00:57:22.504
There is one place Alicent goes

679
00:57:22.505 --> 00:57:25.542
outside the castle walls...

680
00:57:26.276 --> 00:57:28.545
where you may yet
find her alone.

681
00:57:49.532 --> 00:57:51.834
Stop. Search the carts.

682
00:57:56.206 --> 00:57:57.940
What's your business here?

683
00:57:57.941 --> 00:58:01.511
Move 'em on through.
move 'em on through.

684
01:00:23.853 --> 01:00:26.121
No. no. Shh.

685
01:00:26.122 --> 01:00:28.224
- What...
- Shh.

686
01:00:28.791 --> 01:00:31.628
- What... H...
- I must speak with you.

687
01:00:35.932 --> 01:00:38.400
If I c-cry out?

688
01:00:38.401 --> 01:00:39.434
Your knights would find me.

689
01:00:39.435 --> 01:00:41.603
I would be taken or slain.

690
01:00:41.604 --> 01:00:43.405
though not before I killed you.

691
01:00:43.406 --> 01:00:46.409
And then what?

692
01:00:47.043 --> 01:00:48.244
W...

693
01:00:50.380 --> 01:00:53.650
I have begun badly.

694
01:01:05.528 --> 01:01:08.397
We watched the tourney
together. you and I...

695
01:01:08.398 --> 01:01:11.267
the day my brother was born.

696
01:01:12.669 --> 01:01:15.437
We knew. even then. that
men trained up for battle

697
01:01:15.438 --> 01:01:19.676
are eager to fight. to
seek blood and glory.

698
01:01:20.043 --> 01:01:22.045
But you are...

699
01:01:23.680 --> 01:01:27.116
I know you do not have
that desire within you.

700
01:01:33.222 --> 01:01:35.457
Rhaenys has counseled me.

701
01:01:35.458 --> 01:01:40.196
She said she saw in you a wish to
avert the worst of what may now come.

702
01:01:42.999 --> 01:01:46.501
So. you've come
to surrender then?

703
01:01:46.502 --> 01:01:51.474
I have come to see if we may
uncover some path towards peace.

704
01:01:52.642 --> 01:01:55.477
My dragons are restless.
They smell battle.

705
01:01:55.478 --> 01:01:57.846
But if you and I
may come to terms...

706
01:01:57.847 --> 01:02:00.149
There are no terms now.

707
01:02:01.517 --> 01:02:02.918
You have no army.

708
01:02:02.919 --> 01:02:04.986
your allies turn from you when
they hear of your depravity.

709
01:02:04.987 --> 01:02:06.822
your hands are bloodied in
a crime I could never have

710
01:02:06.823 --> 01:02:10.459
- imagined you...
- The trespass was not mine.

711
01:02:10.460 --> 01:02:12.061
Ah. think what you will.

712
01:02:12.628 --> 01:02:15.163
I am a mother too and you have yet
to answer for the murder of my son.

713
01:02:15.164 --> 01:02:18.735
- I repudiate that act with all my heart.
- Of course. you do.

714
01:02:19.302 --> 01:02:22.805
And the usurping of my
rightful inheritance?

715
01:02:39.589 --> 01:02:40.922
Have you now stooped so low

716
01:02:40.923 --> 01:02:42.524
that you will
countenance the suffering

717
01:02:42.525 --> 01:02:44.159
and death of thousands.

718
01:02:44.160 --> 01:02:45.694
in order that your
feckless son...

719
01:02:45.695 --> 01:02:47.896
Your father changed his mind.

720
01:02:47.897 --> 01:02:49.297
Oh. so you say.

721
01:02:49.298 --> 01:02:52.200
And so your father has
proclaimed to the realm.

722
01:02:52.201 --> 01:02:54.971
I saw the king that night.

723
01:02:55.438 --> 01:02:56.805
Mere hours before I left him.

724
01:02:56.806 --> 01:02:59.107
he had affirmed my
right to the throne.

725
01:02:59.108 --> 01:03:01.943
a right he upheld steadfastly.

726
01:03:01.944 --> 01:03:04.881
every day of his life
after my mother died.

727
01:03:06.182 --> 01:03:08.350
And yet. you will maintain
that his mind was changed

728
01:03:08.351 --> 01:03:10.520
- in an instant?
- I will.

729
01:03:11.854 --> 01:03:14.256
You lie.

730
01:03:14.257 --> 01:03:16.125
No. Rhaenyra.

731
01:03:18.895 --> 01:03:20.997
My father loved me. Alicent.

732
01:03:21.464 --> 01:03:23.866
And I believe he loved you. too.

733
01:03:25.368 --> 01:03:27.570
Did you betray him
at the very last?

734
01:03:29.005 --> 01:03:30.972
When was your plan first laid?

735
01:03:30.973 --> 01:03:34.943
Was your ambition so keen...
He changed his mind. Rhaenyra.

736
01:03:34.944 --> 01:03:36.746
He changed his mind.

737
01:03:40.850 --> 01:03:44.487
I swear this to you on
the memory of my mother.

738
01:03:48.291 --> 01:03:51.294
I have been. at times.
unkind. but never untrue.

739
01:03:51.661 --> 01:03:53.295
I pronounced before all
gathered in that room

740
01:03:53.296 --> 01:03:55.932
that you would
make a fine queen.

741
01:03:56.699 --> 01:03:58.901
Do you think me capable
of such naked deceit?

742
01:04:19.555 --> 01:04:21.924
What did he say. at the end?

743
01:04:25.061 --> 01:04:27.430
Did he speak my name?

744
01:04:47.383 --> 01:04:49.118
He was weary.

745
01:04:51.387 --> 01:04:54.223
It was hard. at
times. to understand.

746
01:04:56.158 --> 01:04:57.960
But he spoke Aegon's name.

747
01:05:06.135 --> 01:05:07.836
He said he was the
prince that was promised

748
01:05:07.837 --> 01:05:09.438
to unite the realm.

749
01:05:10.373 --> 01:05:12.140
- What?
- I desire peace as you do.

750
01:05:12.141 --> 01:05:15.277
- but if...
- Did my father use those words?

751
01:05:15.278 --> 01:05:16.578
The Prince That Was Promised?

752
01:05:19.048 --> 01:05:20.482
Did he?

753
01:05:20.483 --> 01:05:22.285
Yes. he did.

754
01:05:25.288 --> 01:05:29.257
He... spoke to you of
the Song of Ice and Fire?

755
01:05:36.299 --> 01:05:39.435
It's a story he once told...

756
01:05:40.102 --> 01:05:42.805
about Aegon the Conqueror.

757
01:05:48.077 --> 01:05:50.212
The C... The Conqueror.

758
01:06:07.630 --> 01:06:09.397
You must go before
you are discovered.

759
01:06:09.398 --> 01:06:11.566
- There's been a mistake.
- There's been no mistake.

760
01:06:11.567 --> 01:06:12.702
Please.

761
01:06:14.403 --> 01:06:16.572
You can prevent this. Alicent.

762
01:06:18.007 --> 01:06:20.041
A terrible war is looming.

763
01:06:20.042 --> 01:06:21.543
and even victory
may be so bloody

764
01:06:21.544 --> 01:06:22.944
as to be counted a loss.

765
01:06:22.945 --> 01:06:27.516
- Do not let your pride blind...
- There's been no mistake.

766
01:06:30.820 --> 01:06:33.089
My father is gone from court.

767
01:06:34.323 --> 01:06:36.525
Cole is on the march. Aemond...

768
01:06:38.861 --> 01:06:40.830
you know what Aemond is.

769
01:06:47.203 --> 01:06:49.839
- It's too late. Rhaenyra.
- Alicent.
